OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776798669
OL,3,CDisgraced Starmer aide denies claim No
OL,4,C10 pushed to get him ambassador role
OL,6,FHe said he had written to Starmer,
OL,7,Fwarning him not to appoint Doyle to
OL,8,Fthe Lords due to his connections.
OL,10,F"He ignored those warnings, and now it
OL,11,Fturns out he had even higher hopes for
OL,12,FDoyle," he wrote on X.
OL,14,FSpeaking at an emergency debate in the
OL,15,FHouse of Commons, Conservative leader
OL,16,FKemi Badenoch said the revelation from
OL,17,FRobbins was proof that Mandelson's
OL,18,Fappointment "wasn't a one-off."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776798669
OL,3,CDisgraced Starmer aide denies claim No
OL,4,C10 pushed to get him ambassador role
OL,6,F"We now know that Mandelson wasn't a
OL,7,Fone-off, according to Sir Olly
OL,8,FRobbins, No 10 also asked for the
OL,9,Fdisgraced Matthew Doyle, the Prime
OL,10,FMinister's then director of
OL,11,Fcommunications, to be made an
OL,12,Fambassador.
OL,14,F"Astonishingly, the prime minister's
OL,15,Foffice even told Robbins to keep this
OL,16,Frequest a secret from the foreign
OL,17,Fsecretary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
